--- title: Catalyst Mixing author: Carl Julius Martensen date: last-modified categories: - ODE - Chemical Engineering description: This example introduces Corleone. engines: ['julia'] julia: exeflags: ["--project=.."] format: html: default ipynb: default --- ::: {#2 .cell execution_count=1} ``` {.julia .cell-code} using Corleone using Corleone.ModelingToolkit using Corleone.ModelingToolkit: t_nounits as t, D_nounits as D using CairoMakie using Corleone.Symbolics ``` ::: ::: {#4 .cell execution_count=1} ``` {.julia .cell-code} function Catalyst(; name::Symbol) vars = @variables begin x(..) = 1., [tunable=false] y(..) = 0., [tunable = false] u(..) = 0.0, [input = true, bounds = (0, 1)] end cons=[] eqs = [ D(x(t)) ~ u(t) * (10 * y(t) - x(t)) D(y(t)) ~ u(t) * (x(t) - 10 * y(t)) - (1 - u(t)) * y(t) ] costs = [ -1 + x(1) + y(1) ] return ODESystem( eqs, t, costs = costs, constraints = cons, consolidate = (x...) -> first(x)[1], name = name ) end ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display execution_count=1} ``` Catalyst (generic function with 1 method) ``` ::: ::: ::: {#6 .cell execution_count=1} ``` {.julia .cell-code} catatlyst = Catalyst(; name = :Catalyst) ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display execution_count=1} ::: {.ansi-escaped-output} ```{=html}

Hence we use display update_theme!(theme_light()); f_light = result_plot_catalyst(optimization_problem, optimization_solution.u) display(f_light) update_theme!(theme_dark()); f_dark = result_plot_catalyst(optimization_problem, optimization_solution.u) ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display} ```{=html} ``` ::: ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display execution_count=1} ```{=html} ``` ::: ::: ## Appendix This document was rendered using Quarto CLI {{< version >}}. ::: {#20 .cell execution_count=1} ``` {.julia .cell-code code-fold="true"} using Pkg versioninfo() Pkg.status() ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ::: {.ansi-escaped-output} ```{=html}
